cc:Work.dc:description:
[Single panel showing the Unix man page for a hypothetical "Brexit" command]
NAME brexit - disconnect from local peers
SYNOPSIS brexit [type=(hard|soft)]
DESCRIPTION Brexit drops connections with machines on the LAN and hardens firewall rules to restrict foreign packets from entering the machine. It then tries to negotiate links with machines on the WAN instead, even if those links are of a lower quality.
While this process is running, any request for quotas may return an erroneous value of 350MB, which may mislead some users into thinking that the local machine is providing significantly more resources to the LAN than it receives in return.
The type parameter determines whether all connections are dropped, or some are maintained. As of the March 2017 release "soft" is no longer an option.
Warning: This command may take a very, very long time to complete.
